### IPC Analysis (module name as positional arg, NOT db_path)

IPC scripts take a **module name** (e.g. `wuapi.dll`) or an IPC identifier
(CLSID, UUID, WinRT class name) as the first positional argument -- never
a `<db_path>`. Exceptions are noted below.

#### COM interface analysis

```
resolve_com_server.py       <module_or_clsid> [--context <ctx>] [--json]
map_com_surface.py          [<module>] [--system-wide] [--top N] [--tier critical|high|medium|low] [--context <ctx>] [--privileged-only] [--json]
enumerate_com_methods.py    <module_or_clsid> [--interface <name>] [--show-pseudo-idl] [--json]
classify_com_entrypoints.py [<module>] [--system-wide] [--context <ctx>] [--json]
audit_com_security.py       <module_or_clsid> [--context <ctx>] [--json]
find_com_privesc.py         [--context <ctx>] [--top N] [--include-uac] [--json]
```

#### RPC interface analysis

```
resolve_rpc_interface.py    <module> [--with-stubs] [--json]
map_rpc_surface.py          [<module>] [--system-wide] [--top N] [--tier critical|high|medium|low] [--servers-only] [--with-blast-radius] [--json]
audit_rpc_security.py       <db_path> [--depth N] [--json]                          # exception: takes db_path
