```

## Module-Wide Vulnerability Scanning

When the user asks to "scan for vulnerabilities", "find bugs", "run security
scanners", or any similar module-wide request, use the `/scan` command (which
runs `run_security_scan.py` with all 6 phases including auto-verification and
deduplication):

```bash
python .agent/agents/security-auditor/scripts/run_security_scan.py <db_path> --goal scan --json
```

Do **NOT** run individual scanner scripts (`scan_auth_bypass.py`,
`scan_logic_flaws.py`, `scan_buffer_overflows.py`, etc.) directly for
module-wide sweeps -- those produce unverified, unfiltered output with high
false-positive rates.  Individual scripts are appropriate only for:

- Targeted single-function analysis (`--function <name>` or `--id <N>`)
- When the user explicitly asks for a specific scanner by name
- When debugging or developing scanner improvements

#### WinRT interface analysis

